news.title: Indore: 70 plot buyers of Satellite Hills to get possession
news.para: According to ADM Abhay Bedekar, a team of revenue officials on Friday laid a line of lime-powder as marking of plots in Satellite Hills to provide the possession to around 70-72 buyers on Monday.

news.title: Mumbai: Delays in okaying increased cost for Metro 3 line leave officials worried
news.para: The cost of the underground Metro-3 project has escalated by over Rs 10,000 crore to Rs 33,406 crore from the original estimate of Rs 23,136 crore in 2011.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Developers fail to repay Rs 1.64 crore loan, case filed
news.para: In his complaint Vishal Mir (27), a resident of Vinjol, has stated that he was working as business development manager with a home loan company.

news.title: Chandigarh: Installation of machines in C&D waste plant to start soon
news.para: ​After an intensive exercise over the past several months, the Chandigarh Municipal Corporation has received and cleared public objections received for the policy, which has been subsequently sent to the Chandigarh administration for final notification.

news.title: RLDA invites bids for development on railways land near Patna junction
news.para: The colony falls under the jurisdiction of Danapur division of East Central Railway (ECR). However, the entire site location is likely to be under the jurisdiction of Patna Municipal Corporation (PMC) as per the Patna Master Plan 2031.

news.title: Mumbai: Redevelopment stuck near Juhu airport as AAI reintroduces height restrictions
news.para: This is not the only residential society to be left in the lurch by a revision of the height limit. JT Radhakrishna, regional executive director, AAI, said the height restriction has been revised for 25 buildings in the Juhu-D N Nagar Andheri area.

news.title: HC gives Stylish Holmes' director three-day relief from ED's Emaar trial
news.para: Though CBI had initially made him an accused, later it turned him as its witness following his decision to become an approver. CBI court too allowed the request of the agency and changed his status from an accused to a witness.

news.title: China Evergrande's offshore debt, assets could be separated in restructuring: Report
news.para: Financial intelligence provider REDD said on Friday the provincial government in Guangdong, where Evergrande is based, aimed to release a framework debt restructuring plan by March that could also wipe out the 60% stake of the group's chairman.

news.title: Scrap plan to have consultant for salt pan land: Jitendra Awhad to MMRDA
news.para: On Wednesday, MMRDA had received bids to appoint a consultant but a day later environment minister Aaditya Thackeray and Awhad opposed the move, saying no residential or commercial construction will be allowed on salt pan land in the city.

news.title: Gurugram: Owner booked for flouting building norms
news.para: In this case, officials said, the developer constructed multiple dwelling units on each floor and sold it to different people. In July last year, the DTCP revoked the occupation certificate (OC) granted to the building.

news.title: Cidco serves eviction notices on over 250 illegal structures
news.para: Cidco has also warned prospective home buyers to refrain from any property transaction in these unauthorised constructions.

news.title: Pune: Property tax defaulters skirt amnesty scheme
news.para: The civic body has collected around Rs35.18 crore via this scheme in a fortnight’s time. The deadline to submit proposals is January 26.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Tax defaulters get auction notice of seized properties
news.para: ​Meanwhile, the civic body has confiscated open plots and properties of 119 big tax defaulters at various nodes for their failure to pay the arrears with penalty and even respond to earlier notices.

news.title: Property registration rates in Telangana may go up by 20%-50%
news.para: The Telangana government is considering hiking property registration charges by 20% to 50% for both agricultural and non-agricultural properties. If the cabinet approves the proposal, the revised charges will come into effect from February 1.

news.title: Over 740 online applications cleared in three weeks: Greater Noida authority
news.para: The majority of the applications were received for the builder and residential-related departments. And most complaints were made through the Mitra mobile app.
